node.text:
Taking self portraits up a notch! #ad I was at @michaelsstores recently and found these amazing new Creatology foam shape people that I knew would be the perfect back-to-school project!

I love that there's such a great variety of skin tones included, which will make it easy for children to create their own little person that looks just like them! Just hand your students some materials and let their creativity shine!

You can find everything you need for this project at @michaelsstores.

Did you know that teachers can save 15% on their entire purchase year round? Just show your badge and you're good to go!

Link in profile to shop: https://bit.ly/36KYdYx

#MakeItWithMichaels
#MichaelsTeacher

node.text:
80-90% off?! 🤯🙌🏽

Several teacher authors and I teamed up to build some special back-to-school bundles that are on deep discount!

The only bummer is that they are only available for a few days! 🗓

There are four special bundles to choose from:
⭐️ K-1st
⭐️ 2nd-3rd
⭐️ 4th-5th
⭐️ K-5th

The K-5 bundle is 90% off and includes everything from all those bundles PLUS 8 bonus resources! 🎉

7/22/21- ETA: congrats to @mrsdelaneymartin! You have won a bundle and some Starbucks cash! 🎉 

I’m linking these bundles in my profile: https://courses.easyteachingtools.com/a/2147491503/gK32m3CP

node.text: Teacher Tip ✨ Keep all your progress monitoring resources in ONE place! I remember I used to run around my class looking for the booklets, my timer, or a pencil, and it added so much extra stress into my life. This bin took care of all those problems! I’m linking this kit in my profile for anyone that might need one for this year: http://bit.ly/progressmonitoringresources

Wednesday is the LAST DAY to purchase your ticket for the virtual Classroom Environment and Design Conference!!!

This is your opportunity to learn about all things classroom environment, design, atmosphere, and decor.

When you purchase, you’ll have immediate access AND lifetime access to all of the sessions, 24+ free bonus resources, and a chance to win a classroom makeover!

node.text:
Did you know that I’m holding some fun giveaways throughout the month of July in my stories? Come join us today and vote for tomorrow’s giveaway! My favorite sharpener or some fun teacher pens? Which will it be? Come share your opinion!

The winning teacher fave will be tomorrow’s prize!

P.S. These giveaways are super easy to enter. No following, commenting, or anything else required. Just slide an emoji over and you are entered!

They’re just a fun way to celebrate the last month of summer with you!

So go vote now and tune into tomorrow’s stories for the giveaway! The winner will also be announced in stories. ❤️

node.text: Summer is the perfect time to prep for birthdays! 🧁 I always get asked what I put inside these birthday bags. I’m linking a blog post in my bio that includes pictures and links to everything! http://bit.ly/bdayblogpost

Anyone else fall in love with this size bin last year? 🎯 didn’t bring this size back, but I found the exact same size in these fun colors at @michaelsstores this week! I took a picture of the label for you (scroll left) in case you’re searching for them this summer.
